sentences: Tommy Castro (born April 15, 1955, San Jose, California, United States) is an American blues, R&B, and rock guitarist and singer.
His popularity was marked by his winning the 2008 Blues Music Award for Entertainer of the Year.

Castro began playing guitar at the age of 10 and was influenced and inspired by electric blues, Chicago blues, West Coast blues, soul music, 1960s rock and roll and Southern rock.
He began playing professionally in Bay Area cover-song bands in the 1970s.
In the 1980s he joined the Warner Bros. Records' band The Dynatones.
In San Francisco, he began playing with North Beach musicians in the 1980s.
Since 1991, he has led his own bands, featuring a drummer, a bass guitar player, and a saxophone player (Keith Crossan has held the saxophone position for many years).
